line.comment: * Arrays used in here:
* Client:
* 0 - Client: station or ship
* 1 - To: table, key is resource, value is number of the resource that is missing
* 2 - From: table, key is resource, value is number of the resource that we want to get rid of
* 3 - High: array of resources that need to be dealt with at high priority
* 4 - Normal: array of resources that need to be dealt with at normal priority.
* 5 - Incoming: table, key is resource, value is number of the resource in incoming trucks.
* 6 - FromVolume: volume of wares that need transporting from here.
* 7 - FromVolumeIncoming: volume of trucks incoming, counts a truck between the truck starting moving and unload.
* Keys in the $ulState table:
* ver - version
* claimAllFactories - 1 or 0, should we claim all factories?
* Clients - table, key: station or ship, value Client
* HighPrio - array of Client with high prio needs
* NormalPrio - array of Client with normal prio needs
* TrucksAll - array of all ships
* Log - array of strings
* TradeBlock - table of wares, value is a counter of how many times in buy/sell attempts (one loop of main loop here) that we ignore the ware before trying to buy/sell it again.
* TruckJobs: table, truck to current job.
* Clients and trucks are tracked in $ulState and not as a local variable on truck/stations so that we can handle them dying a bit more gracefully.
* Deal with deaths.
* Unload recently docked trucks. This will also set FreeTrucks if there are any trucks available for work and update fromvolumeincoming on clients.
* table(ware)->number of prio wares that didn't have trucks that could handle them.
* Deal with prio needs
* Create an array of clients that can provide the most wares that we need.
* Account for incoming volume
* don't waste time if we'll only fill 20% of a reasonably sized truck
* better to use the truck for buy/sell. 40k is a dumb TL filter
* $truck, $fromClient, $toClient
* only one truck to fetch per cycle
* XXX - this function is horribly wasteful.
* Check wares in logistics dock
* Keep track of all wares above 150% of capacity
* unemployed truck docked at homedock.
* Only attempt trading with stuff once every 50 loops.
* This is to prevent trying to sell the same thing over and over again.
* If selling this ware fails, we'll just try some other ware on the next tick.
* If we couldn't find a station to sell to, try smaller amount, but we prefer to unload over max profits
* $fromClient, $toClient, $truck, $ware, $amount
* $truck, $toStation, $buyWare, $sellWare, $amount
* Only send one sell truck per tick.
* $client is the client array
* Logi dock eats all and serves all, even if we starve.
* TODO - figure out if we're dealing with food and set high prio.
* Can't do better than to brutally reset this and it will eventually resync, might get some double deliveries until that happens.
* When making a job, we can't allow the ship to load itself. We have to do the loading for it,
* otherwise we'd have to keep track of all the allocated and unallocated wares in the stations
* and that would be too much pain.
* Rules for trucks:
* - trucks can only be added when they are homebased and docked at the logi dock.
* - truck that is docked somewhere stays docked there until it's needed somewhere else.
* - trucks don't get jobs for "go to X, load Y, go to Z". Trucks get jobs like "go to X", "go to Y".
* the job of loading and unloading them falls on this script after they are docked there.
* - trucks get recalled to the logi dock to try to keep a reserve of 20% trucks there.
* - when a truck is docked somewhere we don't care about the priority of the needs,
* if the truck has a ware, it unloads it. Otherwise we might end up with trucks bouncing around
* priority targets never getting anything done.
* Job = array
* 0 - station, destination station
* 1 - sell job, ware
* 2 - buy job, ware
* 3 - trade job, amount
* I really wish I could write $client.FromVolumeIncoming += $truck->get cargo bay size
* Trucks that are somewhere that's not a client.
* Something else deals with them.
* This can happen when a truck died en route and we brutally reset it, nothing we can do about it.
* XXX - we should probably set high/normal prio after emptying trucks.
* $ware, $amount, $client
* some wares could have already been handled and we could not update the prio arrays for them.
* $client contains the destination client, $bestClient contains the source client.
* $fromClient, $toClient, $truck, $ware, $amount
* $LogEntry = sprintf: fmt='No truck for %s. (%s %s)', $ware, $checked, $notbusy, null, null
* gosub Log:
* $toClient, $truck
* sets CanTruckJump if the truck has enough fuel to jump to toClient and then back to logistics dock
* $fromClient, $toClient, $truck, $ware, $amount
* $truck, $fromClient, $toClient, $whyFly
* Before sending the truck to the destination, load it with other stuff we might need there.
* reset until next time
* $truck, $toStation, $buyWare, $sellWare, $amount
* reset sellware and buyware to not confuse things on the next call
* $truck, $fromClient, $whyFly
* $LogEntry
